                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d410">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6412: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin (<persName type="from"
                            >Lockhart</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-01T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 1 [<hi rend="italic">3?</hi>], 1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received
                        July 3—5:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A special train having on board 132 Japanese soldiers, fully armed, and
                    approximately 50 railway police, all Chinese and armed only with revolvers, left
                    for Tangshan this morning ostensibly to open traffic on railway. A number of
                    railway workmen accompanied train. So far as can be ascertained no arrangements
                    have been made with Li Chi-chun’s forces for passage of train through their
                    territory and there is accordingly possibility of clash. Reliably informed
                    Chinese managing director of railway originated plan and made proposal to
                    Japanese. Japanese commandant offered American, British and French commanders on
                        Saturday<note n="87" xml:id="d410fn87">July 1.</note> officially to share in
                        <pb facs="0472" n="370" xml:id="pg_370"/> responsibility of operating train
                    but offer was declined. Japanese commandant also inquired of each commander
                    whether any objection to proposal and received negative reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
